<li><a href="http://www.siggraph.org/education/materials/HyperGraph/radiosity/overview_1.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.siggraph.org/education/materials/HyperGraph/radiosity/overview_1.htm" rel="nofollow">Radiosity Overview, from HyperGraph of SIGGRAPH</a> (provides full matrix radiosity algorithm and progressive radiosity algorithm)</li>
<li><a href="http://freespace.virgin.net/hugo.elias/radiosity/radiosity.htm" class="external text" title="http://freespace.virgin.net/hugo.elias/radiosity/radiosity.htm" rel="nofollow">Radiosity, by Hugo Elias</a> (also provides a general overview of lighting algorithms, along with programming examples)</li>
<li><a href="http://web.cs.wpi.edu/~matt/courses/cs563/talks/radiosity.html" class="external text" title="http://web.cs.wpi.edu/~matt/courses/cs563/talks/radiosity.html" rel="nofollow">Radiosity, by Allen Martin</a> (a slightly more mathematical explanation of radiosity)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cse.iitd.ernet.in/~parag/projects/CG2/asign2/report/RADical.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.cse.iitd.ernet.in/~parag/projects/CG2/asign2/report/RADical.shtml" rel="nofollow">RADical, by Parag Chaudhuri</a> (an implementation of shooting &amp; sorting variant of progressive radiosity algorithm with OpenGL acceleration, extending from GLUTRAD by Colbeck)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.tralvex.com/pub/rover/abs-mnu.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.tralvex.com/pub/rover/abs-mnu.htm" rel="nofollow">ROVER, by Tralvex Yeap</a> (Radiosity Abstracts &amp; Bibliography Library)</li>
<li><a href="http://dudka.cz/rrv" class="external text" title="http://dudka.cz/rrv" rel="nofollow">Radiosity Renderer and Visualizer</a> (simple implementation of radiosity renderer based on <a href="/wiki/OpenGL" title="OpenGL">OpenGL</a>)</li>
</ul>


